Hello
I am 30 years old.
I started doing coke at 20 years old,
I never took it every day, I wasn't super addicted.
I used to take it 1 or 2 times a month at most, but for about 6 months or even a year now, I can control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even though before I promised myself not to go get some shnouf, after 2 or 3 drinks I start to get hot and I think, "come on, we only have one life, it's partiiii" and it's impossible to control myself, I want to take more.
So here, I know the problem is alcohol at its core, but it's crazy, impossible to stop among family and friends for the apero, etc.
Has anyone this problem?
Thank you
stop drinking and the problem will be solved
sometimes you have to be violent with yourself to stop ...
have you at least talked to your family doctor about it?
seeing an addict might do you some good, especially for "evaluating" your consumption
In fact, it's in the evening that it's hardest to hold on mentally.
the day is going well
Hello,
I am politox with a big problem of alcoholism,
I have been sober from alcohol for a few years, but I can't convince myself that I will never drink another drop of alcohol, even though I want to, maybe not enough willpower.
I sometimes have to restart on occasions because it's stronger than me, and as soon as I start, it's impossible for me to stop.
after I sleep very badly and I am sick the next day and especially I hate myself,
I'm ashamed of who I become when I've been drinking and I suffer from it.
I can't drink normally.
I drink all my dry glasses.
why do I have this connection with alcohol when so many people can drink normally??
I haven't drunk anything for 10 days.
this weekend i am invited to a birthday party and i am very very scared,
If you understand me, have gone through the same thing or have passed the threshold, I will take anything that can help me.
Thank you for reading me and I look forward to your responses.
